p: Oxygenated monoterpenes (42.06%, 40.82%, and 31.75% for S1, S3, and S2, respectively) are the dominant constituents, followed by monoterpene hydrocarbons (31.33%, 23.59%, and 20.16% for S2, S3, and S1, respectively), and sesquiterpene hydrocarbons (27.64%, 21.88%, and 20.13% for S1, S3, and S2, respectively). Camphor (16.84%) and 1,8-cineole (9.86%) are the most abundant constituents of S1 oil, followed by α-thujone (9.26%) ( Figure 1). Camphor (16.16%), β-pinene (9.14%), and 1,8-cineole (8.80%) are the dominant compounds in S2 oil.
